==Hebrew==
===Etymology===
Feminine derivation of [[עבר]] (Heber). A Jewish woman.

No. It comes from the word Ivri (hebrew) which is connected to Ovar which means "cross over" Abraham was called an Ivri because he was from among those who crossed over into Canaan (it was a word for immigrant) The language of this particular "Ivri" was ''עברית''' ie: "Ivrit"

===Noun===
'''עברית'''

# The original [[Hebrew]] language of the [[Bible]] and the first official language of [[Israel]].

